title: Przyborowice, Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship
text:
Przyborowice is a <a href="village">village</a> in the administrative district of <a href="Gmina%20Bogoria">Gmina Bogoria</a>, within <a href="Stasz%C3%B3w%20County">Staszów County</a>, <a href="%C5%9Awi%C4%99tokrzyskie%20Voivodeship">Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship</a>, in south-central Poland. It lies approximately north-west of <a href="Bogoria%2C%20Poland">Bogoria</a>, north-east of <a href="Stasz%C3%B3w">Staszów</a>, and south-east of the regional capital <a href="Kielce">Kielce</a>.
The village has a population of 260.
Demography.
According to the <a href="Polish%20census%20of%202002">2002 Poland census</a>, there were 266 people residing in Przyborowice village, of whom 51.9% were male and 48.1% were female. In the village, the population was spread out, with 29.3% under the age of 18, 36.1% from 18 to 44, 13.2% from 45 to 64, and 21.4% who were 65 years of age or older.
